Let's KnowLet's KnowWe all are fascinated by the wonders of nature. The high mountains, the 
limitless oceans, vast deserts, the outer space etc. have always attracted men 
despite the risk and danger involved in getting there. Adventures and 
explorations are a way of testing human strength. Any activity which involves 
risk, danger and uncertain experiences is called an adventure. Adventure 
sports and adventure tourism have become very popular in present times. The 
people who participate in these activities need to have true determination and 
the spirit of adventure.

Adventure of MountaineeringClimbing mountains is called mountaineering. Those who climb mountains for 
adventure are called mountaineers. Every year, hundreds of climbers, both men 
and women, climb the most difficult mountains all around the world. India is 
famous for the Himalayas, the world's highest mountain range. World's highest 
mountain peak, Mount Everest (8848m), which is in Nepal, also belong to the 
Himalayas. It attracts adventure seekers from all over the world. People climb 
mountains for the sake of adventure and also to explore the things around. Scaling 
a mountain peak also gives the sense of victory to a climber. 
Many mountaineers dreamt of scaling Mount Everest but it was Sir Edmund Hillary 
of New Zealand and Sherpa Tenzing Norgay of Nepal who reached first to the top of 
peak on 29 May 1953. Later in 1984, Bachendri Pal was the first Indian woman to 
climb the Mount Everest.
Bachendri Pal– The rough and tough woman Bachendri Pal was the first Indian 
woman and the fifth woman in the world to climb the Mount Everest on 23 May 
1984. Prior to this, she also climbed the Gangotri and Rudragaria peaks. India is 
proud of her. She has been awarded with the Padma Shri and Arjuna awards. 
Environmental Studies-5135

Key termsKey termsKey termsMountaineering training– As we go higher up on the mountains, the oxygen in the 
air becomes less. Therefore, breathing gets difficult and the person feels tired. 
There is also the problem of getting drinking water as the temperature is very low 
at the higher altitudes. So, it is necessary to undergo training before going on a 
mountain expedition. In our country, the Himalayan Mountaineering Institute in 
Darjeeling and the Nehru Institute of Mountaineering in Uttarkashi provide 
training to mountaineers.
Climbing equipment– A mountaineer requires ice-axe, helmet, nylon ropes, 
aluminium ladder, oxygen cylinder and crampons while climbing on mountains. 
Other than these, a mountaineer needs to carry lightweight thermal clothing, 
waterproof jacket, torch, first aid kit, emergency food etc. 
Santosh Yadav is the only woman in the world to climb the Mount Everest twice 
once in 1992 and then in 1993.

The EarthEarth is the only planet known to have life on it. It is surrounded by a layer of air 
called atmosphere. The atmosphere contains gases such as oxygen, nitrogen and 
carbon dioxide. All living things need oxygen to live. Our Earth is also called the Blue 
Planet. This is because when astronauts first saw the Earth from space, it looked 
blue due to the presence of water on it.

About three-fourht of Earth's surface is covered with water and one-fourth by land.

(Knowledge)Humans in SpaceHuman beings have always wanted to know about the mysteries of the sky. This 
motivated them to travel into space. Science has helped them to travel into space 
in a spacecraft.
Yuri Gagarin was the first man to go into space on 12 April, 
1961. He was a Soviet Cosmonaut who orbited the Earth in 
the spacecraft called Vostok 1.
Valentina Tereshkova was the first woman to go into space 
(1963).
Environmental Studies-5141

On 21 July 1969, US astronaut Neil Armstrong became the 
first person to land on the surface of the moon. He went 
there in the spacecraft Apollo 11.
Sunita Williams, an American astronaut of Indian origin, has 
set up world record for spending more than 50 hours on space 
walk alone. She has spent a total of 322 days in space.
Indians in SpaceOn 3rd April 1984 Squardon Leader Rakesh Sharma became the first Indian to go 
into space. He along with two Russian astronauts, went into space in a spacecraft 
called Soyuz T-11. In his conversation with the then Prime Minister Mrs Indira 
Gandhi, from space, he described India as 'Saare Jahan Se Achcha' which means 
'The best in the world'.
It was a moment of pride and glory for Indians. Rakesh Sharma was awarded the 
Ashoka Chakra for his achievement.
Kalpana Chawla became the first Indian woman to go into space. She went on first 
space flight as a part of NASA space program on 19 November 1997. In January 
2003, she went on her second space mission, in the space shuttle Columbia along 
with six other astronauts. Unfortunately, the space shuttle exploded merely 16 
minutes before landing back on the Earth on 1 February 2003.
Kalpana and all her co-astronauts died in the explosion.
The space travellers are an inspiration to young people who want to go into space.
The astronauts train hard to learn about space and to adapt themselves to the 
conditions in space. The Mission Control on earth sends spacecrafts with 
astronauts into space by means of rockets.
In space stations, there are separate modules to work and to live. The spacesuits 
that astronauts wear create a small atmosphere around them because there is no 
air in space.
The space shuttle carries the astronauts back to Earth after the completion of their 
mission. The space shuttles can be used again and again, while the rockets can only 
be used once.

Any time when an astronaut gets out of a vehicle while in space, is 
called a space walk.

What is water pollution? 
Water pollution occurs when harmful substances—often chemicals or microorganisms—contaminate a 
stream, river, lake, ocean, aquifer, or other body of water, degrading water quality and rendering it toxic to 
humans or the environment.
The Causes of Water PollutionIndustrial Waste. Industries and industrial sites across the world are a major contributor to water pollution.

Radioactive WasteEnvironmental Studies-5148What is air pollution? 
Air pollution is contamination of the indoor or outdoor environment by any chemical, physical or biological 
agent that modifies the natural characteristics of the atmosphere. Household combustion devices, motor 
vehicles, industrial facilities and forest fires are common sources of air pollution.
The Causes of Air Pollution
! 
Air pollution can be caused by a number of factors, including: Burning fossil fuels.
! 
The burning of coal, oil, and natural gas for power in factories, electrical plants, and automobiles is the 
main cause of air pollution. This process releases solid particles like ash and soot, as well as harmful 
gases. 
! 
The gases emitted from cars, trucks, buses, and other vehicles pollute the environment.
! 
Breeding farm animals can lead to poor air quality, which can negatively impact the nutrient value of 
food. Wildfires and volcanoes.
! 
Industrial chemicals events can also cause air pollution. 
! 
These chemicals can also contribute to air pollution. 
! 
Ozone pollution, also known as smog, is caused by the mixing of volatile organic compounds (VOCs) and 
nitrogen oxides (NOx) with sunlight and heat. This is a common problem in the summer.
